p-content/uploads/2012/08/WCGR12-WebBanners-Sponsor.png" alt="" width="150" height="150" /></a>WordCamp is coming to Grand Rapids, MI this weekend! In just 2 days, Grand Valley State University will be overrun with WordPress enthusiasts spreading lots of WordPress love.</p>\n<p>The Grand Rapids organizers have worked hard to provide everyone with a jam-packed two days of WordPress goodness.</p>\n<p>Saturday, there will be <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/schedule/">4 tracks</a> full of awesome <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/speakers/">speakers</a> that want to share their WordPress knowledge and expertise with you.  The Saturday conference will be followed by an afterparty at the <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/15/party-up/" target="_blank">SpeakEZ Lounge</a>.</p>\n<p>Sunday is <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/16/what-is-wordpress-study-hall/">WordPress Study Hall</a> where the Grand Rapids organizers are combining the  traditional “Dev Day” that follows most WordCamp events with more user- and attendee-focused opportunities.</p>\n<p>Haven&#8217;t got a ticket yet? Don&#8217;t worry because <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/attend/">75 additional tickets</a> were released yesterday and there are plenty still up for grabs! Grand Rapids a little to far for you to travel? You can <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/2012/08/14/cant-make-it-but-still-want-to-join-in-the-fun/">tune in</a> remotely via a developer track livestream.</p>\n<p>For more information on WordCamp Grand Rapids, check out the <a href="http://2012.grandrapids.wordcamp.org/">website</a> or follow them on <a href="https://twitter.com/wcgrandrapids/">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>Last, we want to give a shout out to our newest WDS team member, <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-richards/">Brian Richards</a>, and the organizers who have done so much hard work and planning to bring WordCamp to Western Michigan. We know it&#8217;s going to be a great event!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:81:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/16/wordcamp-grand-rapids-is-just-days-away/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:47:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"Using WordPress to Help Find the Best of the Best";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:86:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:95:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 09 Aug 2012 19:12:46 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15:"Client Websites";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WebDevStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=6709";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:408:"In the past week we have been hard at work launching the Best Of sections for the websites of Philadelphia Magazine and Boston Magazine. Together with magazine publishers, MetroCorp Inc., we worked to create an online directory of their popular &#8230; <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"April Heline";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2053:"<p>In the past week we have been hard at work launching the Best Of sections for the websites of <a href="http://www.phillymag.com/philly/best-of/" target="_blank">Philadelphia Magazine</a> and <a href="http://www.bostonmagazine.com/boston/best-of/" target="_blank">Boston Magazine</a>. Together with magazine publishers, MetroCorp Inc., we worked to create an online directory of their popular Best Of series for Philadelphia Magazine and Boston Magazine, powered by <a title="WordPress Custom Development and Design" href="http://webdevstudios.com/wordpress/">WordPress</a> of course!</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Philly-2012.png" rel="shadowbox[sbpost-6709];player=img;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6702" title="Best of Philly 2012" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Philly-2012.png" alt="" width="1301" height="1289" /></a></p>\n<p>The Best Of series highlights the most popular and highest rated restaurants, businesses, entertainment and services in the area. Each year these two magazines dedicate one issue to Best Of  highlighting the best of the best in the city and surrounding suburbs. The team wanted to create a clean and organized way to search this list on their website and an easy way to add the winners each year.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Boston-2012.png" rel="shadowbox[sbpost-6709];player=img;"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-6705" title="Best of Boston 2012" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Best-of-Boston-2012.png" alt="" width="1301" height="1465" /></a></p>\n<p>The new Best Of section allows the visitor to scroll through a list of categories and view some information including details about the winner, photos from the location, addresses, phone numbers and website.  Powered by a combination of custom post types, custom taxonomies, and WDS magic, the new Best Of sections make finding the Best of the Best that much easier with WordPress!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:91:"http://webdevstudios.com/2012/08/09/using-wordpress-to-help-find-the-best-of-the-best/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:47:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";